F2                              over a word and it modifies the same 
                                words in the file

Ctrl +                          delete to erase a whole line of code

Ctrl + J                        to hide/show the terminal

Ctrl + Shift + O                to global navigate files by name

Ctrl + P                        go to file by name

Ctrl + Shift + F                to globaly find a word in any file

Ctrl + `                        to open and close the terminal

Ctrl + D                        edit multiple lines with the same name, the more
                                you press Ctrl D the more lines it selects

Ctrl + Alt + up down arrow      edit multiple lines that are within the up and down selections

Alt + Click                     edit multiple lines in every click you did